--- !u!114 &899058525
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 899058523}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: b777428ee8b5bca4b8a6821d0477fec7, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::BattleTutorialManager
  tutorialPages:
  - explanationText: 'Welcome to the battle tutorial! Here we will teach you the
      basic of the combat. '
    optionalImage: {fileID: 0}
  - explanationText: This game is using turn based combat system. Each character
      takes turn in doing action to defeat their opponent.
    optionalImage: {fileID: 0}
  - explanationText: 'There is 2 main resources in the combat :

      1. <color=red>Health</color>:
      This is your lifeline, if your Health reaches 0, you are defeated.

      2.
      <color=blue>Mana</color>: This is used to cast skill, and will passively regenerate
      1 mana each turn.'
    optionalImage: {fileID: 21300000, guid: d1c5305f322f5bf449d9e3b4b555b331, type: 3}
  - explanationText: 'There is also 4 type of atribute in your sleeve :

      1.
      <b>STR</b>: Affects your physical attack damage

      2. <b>DEF</b>: Affects
      your damage suffered from physical attack

      3. <b>INT</b>: Affects your
      magic attack damage

      4. <b>RES</b>: Affects your damage suffered from
      magic attack'
    optionalImage: {fileID: 0}
  - explanationText: 'To do actions in your turn, you can click in the coresponding
      menu. Some menu will have sub menu, and the controls are listed down below
      :

      - <b>Single-Left Click</b> on Attack, Skill, or Item to open the sub-menu.

      -
      <b>Double-Left Click</b> on your chosen action (or Defend) to execute it.

      -
      <b>Single-Right Click</b> on a menu to close the sub-menu. '
    optionalImage: {fileID: 638052856891300310, guid: 3814b1729222e9443898ea0440854aea, type: 3}
  - explanationText: You can only do 1 action (Attack, Skill, Defend) per turn. But
      using <b>Item</b> doesn't count as doing action and does not end your turn.
    optionalImage: {fileID: 0}
  tutorialPanel: {fileID: 389403807}
  explanationText: {fileID: 315593062}
  tutorialImage: {fileID: 2077215200}
  pageIndicatorText: {fileID: 1161829075}
  nextButton: {fileID: 413648338}
  nextButtonText: {fileID: 53158276}
  prevButton: {fileID: 1296858448}
